Hello Andrew

On 04-Jan-01, you wrote:

AB> folks, I am writing a program and would like to know what is the
AB> chr$() I use to move the cursor up one line?

The easiest way is to write a small program roughly like this:

OpenWindow
InputFromWindow
OutputToWindow
Loop:
asciivalue.w=asc(inkey$)
NPrint asciivalue
Goto Loop

Then you run it, hit the key you want and use the value with Chr$().

But while I'm here, I may as well tell you that what I think you're
looking for doesn't exist.  The Up Arrow key has a value of 28 ($1C)
or 76 if you wanna use RawKey, but if you print that in a stream of
text I don't think it makes the cursor go up a line.  You'll need to
either 1) relocate the cursor by hand or 2) open a console and use
ANSI sequences.

Somebody else can help you here ;]

