On 03-Jan-01, Andrew Bruno wrote:
> Hi,
> 
> folks, I am writing a program and would like to know what is the
> chr$() I use to move the cursor up one line?

ESC [ x A  -- moves the cursor up x lines while staying in the same
column.

ESC [ x E  -- moves the cursor up x lines and puts it in column 1.

ESC [ r;c f  -- moves the cursor to row r and column c.

