> folks, I am writing a program and would like to know what is the chr$() I
> use to move the cursor up one line?

You need to use Escape codes (assuming you're in a CLI, right? ;)

See this file for a list of escape codes
(http://us.aminet.net/pub/aminet/dev/misc/AmigaANSI.txt), and also the
TextMode function in StatsFuncs (aminet:dev/basic/StatsFuncs.lha).

The source below is an example, though you'll probably have to experiment
quite a bit to get things just how you want 'em ;)

-----------------------

NPrint "Hello"
NPrint "Above line will change in two secs!"

VWait 100

esc$ = Chr$(27) + "["        ; escape character

Print esc$ + "2A" + "Goodbye" ; 2A is an escape code for moving up 2 lines

MouseWait:End

------------------------

Note that I've just edited this in Outlook, so although it seems fine here,
I might've screwed up some minor point!

