OK, have you looked at the RAmiga+Help for OpenSerial?

128 opens the serial with #serf_xdisabled (disables xon/xoff)
129 does the above + #serf_parity_on (enables parity checking)
130 does the same as 128 + #serf_parity_odd (select odd parity)
131 does all of those three combined.

If all you need to do is open in 7 bit mode instead of 8, then yoo
will need to use -THIS- number:

4 - #serf_7wire (use ...

OK, that's 7wire...  is that the same thing?  It isn't, is it...

<RKM time>

I'VE GOT IT!!!  =]

Do -something- like this : (fiddling about with variations, looking in
VIEW NEWTYPES etc might be needed - AND PUT BLITZLIBS:AMIGALIBS.RES
IN YOUR RESIDENTS BOX!!!)

*ioRequest.IOExtSer=OpenSerial("hyperCOM3.device",1,1200,128/whatever:)
If *ioRequest=0
    End
EndIf
*ioRequest\ioReadLen=number of bits in read word not including parity
*ioRequest\ioWriteLen=number of bits in write word (1-8)   "   "   "
*ioRequest\ioStopBits=number of stop bits (0, 1 or 2)

Good luck and hope this helps =]

