Hi Toby

> CE> Hmmm, how about having it generate some Enforcer hits for no

Didn't it do that anyway, the rest of Blitz usually does ;)

> longword from a random location or something.  I was also thinking of

If you want a safe command, just read a longword from 0. It won't crash, 
but it'll cause enforcer hits.

If you want it to crash, try writing a longword to address 4 :)

> doing something that places a random value in A4.  Isn't that the one
> that Blitz uses?  ;] Or just increases it by one or something =]

Blitz uses a4 for local variable space (when you are in 
statements/procedures). a5 is the gloabl variable space (all other 
variables) and a3 is the temporary string buffer. Trashing a3 or a4 could 
easily cause crashes and enforcer hits, trashing a5 would probably cause 
enforcer hits during the program and crashes on exit.


